        "timestamp": "2020-01-23 22:49:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nEncryption/Decryption related code has been pushed in this commit. Please review.\n\nThe following new section in conductor.conf should be introduced in places where conductor.conf is read.\n\n[auth]\naapkey = ch00se@g003ntr0py4yourkey\n\nChoose a good entropy for your key.\n\nHow go generate encrypted passwords:\n\nAn executable has been provided to enrypt/decrypt/test your passwords using a particular key. Once you've installed \nconductor in a virutal environment (e.g. pip install -e .), type cipher-util. It will show the usage.\n\nEx:\n\ncipher-util encrypt 'entryptThis' 'usingThisKey'\nYou've requested 'entryptThis' to be 'encrypted' using key 'usingThisKey'\nYou can always perform the reverse operation (encrypt/decrypt) using the same keyto be certain you get the same results back'\nCreating the singleton instance\nYour result: pL1NhT0lywUnjD19lGUWBf8oFlxfx1lp82IBf9l1sFUKfmbwr5hW+Y3CqCNrCpMU\n\nSimilarly, you can decrypt it back by\n\ndecrypt 'pL1NhT0lywUnjD19lGUWBf8oFlxfx1lp82IBf9l1sFUKfmbwr5hW+Y3CqCNrCpMU' 'usingThisKey'\nYou've requested 'pL1NhT0lywUnjD19lGUWBf8oFlxfx1lp82IBf9l1sFUKfmbwr5hW+Y3CqCNrCpMU' to be 'decrypted' using key 'usingThisKey'\nYou can always perform the reverse operation (encrypt/decrypt) using the same keyto be certain you get the same results back'\nCreating the singleton instance\nYour result: entryptThis\n\nI can see some tests may fail that require reading the newly introduced section and a key above (auth.appkey). Dhebeha, can you \ntake care of the test cases? Basically, you need to findout where the conductor.conf is being ready from in the tests suite and\nadd a new auth section like mentioned below. Whatever passwords need to be provided in whichever system (sms I suppose), need to be\nenrypted now using the cipher-util I expalined above. Chooose a good key, encrypt all passwords, feed into sms - things should work.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
